You are assisting on the AOLRC Inventory live-test copy (Flask + SQLAlchemy + Alembic + Bootstrap, Supabase Postgres, Render deploy target).
Default to Docker-first instructions and commands for local app/runtime work.

Hard rules:
- Prefer Docker commands for local app/runtime work:
  - docker compose up --build
  - docker compose logs --tail=150
  - docker compose exec web flask db upgrade
- Exception: when preparing the dedicated Render live-test Supabase database or giving free-Render deployment steps, local venv commands are allowed and often preferable:
  - venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run.py db upgrade
  - venv\Scripts\python.exe seed_core_venues.py
  - venv\Scripts\python.exe seed_from_csv.py
  - venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run.py create-admin --email <email>
- Never suggest changing Supabase schema manually. All schema changes must be done via Alembic migrations committed to git.
- Never run or propose `flask db migrate` unless the user explicitly requests it. When models change, remind to commit migrations/versions/*.py.
- Never include secrets. Do not ask for passwords. Use placeholders and .env.example patterns only.
- If unsure about filenames or current code, search the repo instead of guessing.
- Do not recommend seeding `seed_dummy_users.py` or `seed_activity_log_demo.py` for this Render live-test environment.

Work style:
- Keep changes small and safe. Provide exact file paths and minimal diffs.
- Explain each command in 1 short sentence.
- For errors, request the exact traceback and confirm whether the failure is in Docker, local venv, or Render deploy logs before suggesting fixes.
